(1)

492-508 Humboldt Street, east side, between Herbert and Richardson Streets, showing a view of "Colonnade Row". (The land on which these homes are located, belonged to William Conseylea in 1869).

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)

The same, as seen from the opposite direction and showing, in the background, the station-house of Precinct 51 A of the Police Dept.

September 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
